        public InternalEndpoint(String name,
                        String protocol,
                        int port)
        Initializes a new instance of the InternalEndpoint class with required arguments.
        Parameters:
        name - Required for each internal endpoint. A unique name for the external endpoint.
        protocol - Required for each internal endpoint. Transport protocol for the endpoint. Its value has to be one of the following: 'tcp', 'udp', 'http', 'https'.
        port - Required for each internal endpoint. The port for the external endpoint. You can specify any port number you choose, but the port number specified must not collide with port numbers occupied by roles in the service. Possible values range between 1 and 65535, inclusive
